void PD_ConnectInitRole ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance,
uint32_t  typecRole,
uint8_t  errorRecovery 
)
1657 {
1658  //state in Type-C Spec
1659  TypeCState_t newState;
1660  uint32_t infoVal;
1661 
1662  newState = pdInstance->curConnectState;
1663  pdInstance->enterAttachedSrcFromAttachWaitSNK = 0;
1664 
1665  /*
1666  The ErrorRecovery state is where the port removes the terminations from the CC1 and CC2
1667  pins for tErrorRecovery followed by transitioning to the appropriate Unattached.SNK or
1668  Unattached.SRC state based on port type. This is the equivalent of forcing a detach event
1669  and looking for a new attach.
1670  */
1671  /* error recovery 两件事
1672  * 1. remove terminations for CC1 and CC2 for tErrorRecovery
1673  * 2. transition to unattached state
1674  */
1675  if (errorRecovery)
1676  {
1677  if (pdInstance->curConnectState != TYPEC_ERROR_RECOVERY)
1678  {
1679  pdInstance->ccUsed = kPD_CCInvalid;
1680  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
1681  pdInstance->curConnectState = TYPEC_ERROR_RECOVERY;
1682  //设置CC，包括Vconn
1683  PD_ConnectSetupNewState(pdInstance, 0);
1684  }
1685 
1686  // 这里是tErrorRecovery的延迟，那么上面是做remove terminations?
1687  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tDelayTimer, T_ERROR_RECOVERY);
1688 
1689  while (!PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tDelayTimer))
1690  {
1691  }
1692  }
1693  // Question: 经过上述操作可以保证state transition to unattached.xxx ?
1694 
1695  // Question: 设置power progress -> stable的作用 ?
1696  /* 以下四种都是初始状态 */
1697  // set phy pwr_inprogress state
1698  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
1699  pdInstance->vbusDischargeInProgress = kVbus_NoDischarge;
1700  pdInstance->ccUsed = kPD_CCInvalid;
1701  pdInstance->curConnectState = TYPEC_DISABLED;
1702 
1703  // set cc initial state according to power role, confirm cc state tendency
1704  newState = PD_ConnectGetInitRoleState(pdInstance, typecRole);
1705  // 注意，这里的curConnectState在上面刚刚被置为TYPEC_DISABLED
1706  if (newState != pdInstance->curConnectState)
1707  {
1708  /* In the process of connecting, just change the role */
1709  if (((newState == TYPEC_UNATTACHED_SNK) && (pdInstance->curConnectState == TYPEC_ATTACH_WAIT_SNK)) ||
1710  ((newState == TYPEC_UNATTACHED_SRC) && (pdInstance->curConnectState == TYPEC_ATTACH_WAIT_SRC)))
1711  {
1712  /* continue the original state machine */
1713  }
1714  /* Not connected */
1715  else
1716  {
1717  if (newState != TYPEC_DISABLED)
1718  {
1719  // get vbus info, save it to infoVal
1720  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_GET_VBUS_POWER_STATE, &infoVal);
1721  if (infoVal & PD_VBUS_POWER_STATE_VSYS_MASK)
1722  {
1723  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_GET_VBUS_POWER_STATE, &infoVal);
1724  if (!(infoVal & PD_VBUS_POWER_STATE_VSAFE0V_MASK))
1725  {
1726  /* VBUS Discharge:
1727  If state is not disabled, and we are not in dead battery, enable vbus discharge on startup */
1728  pdInstance->vbusDischargeInProgress = kVbus_ApplyTypecDischarge;
1729  }
1730  }
1731  }
1732 
1733  pdInstance->curConnectState = newState;
1734  pdInstance->ccUsed = kPD_CCInvalid;
1735  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
1736  PD_ConnectSetupNewState(pdInstance, 1);
1737  }
1738  }
1739 }

1762  }
1763 }

uint8_t PD_MsgGetReceiveResult ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance)
472 {
473  uint8_t retVal = 0;
474  uint32_t receiveLength;
475 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT)
476  uint32_t index;
477  uint8_t *destBuffer;
478  uint8_t *sourceBuffer;
479  uint8_t needCopy = 0;
480  pd_msg_header_t msgHeader;
481  pd_extended_msg_header_t extHeader;
482 #endif
483 
484  if (pdInstance->receiveState == 2)
485  {
486  pdInstance->receiveState = 0;
487  receiveLength = pdInstance->receivedLength;
488 
489 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT)
490  sourceBuffer = (uint8_t *)pdInstance->receivingDataBuffer;
491  sourceBuffer += 2;
492  msgHeader.msgHeaderVal = (uint16_t)(USB_SHORT_FROM_LITTLE_ENDIAN_ADDRESS(sourceBuffer));
493  if (msgHeader.bitFields.extended)
494  {
495  sourceBuffer += 2;
496  extHeader.extendedMsgHeaderVal = (uint32_t)(USB_SHORT_FROM_LITTLE_ENDIAN_ADDRESS(sourceBuffer));
497 
498  /* chunked ext msg need copy, because it may be larger than 28 bytes and are chunked */
499  if ((void *)pdInstance->receivingDataBuffer == (void *)pdInstance->receivingChunkedData)
500  {
501  needCopy = 1;
502 
503  destBuffer = (uint8_t *)pdInstance->receivingData;
504  destBuffer += 4;
505  sourceBuffer = (uint8_t *)pdInstance->receivingDataBuffer;
506  sourceBuffer += 4;
507 
508  destBuffer[0] = sourceBuffer[0]; /* ext header */
509  destBuffer[1] = sourceBuffer[1];
510  destBuffer += 2;
511  sourceBuffer += 2; /* ext header */
512  }
513  else
514  {
515  needCopy = 0;
516  }
517 
518  if ((!extHeader.bitFields.chunked))
519  {
520  /* unchunked ext msg */
521  if (receiveLength > 260)
522  {
523  receiveLength = 260;
524  }
525  }
526  else
527  {
528  /* chunked ext msg */
529  if (receiveLength > 32)
530  {
531  receiveLength = 32;
532  }
533 
534  if (needCopy)
535  {
536  destBuffer += (extHeader.bitFields.chunkNumber * 26);
537  }
538  }
539  }
540  else
541 #endif
542  {
543  if (receiveLength > 32)
544  {
545  receiveLength = 32;
546  }
547  }
548 
549  if (pdInstance->receiveResult == kStatus_PD_Success)
550  {
551 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_EXTENDED_MSG_SUPPORT)
552  if (needCopy)
553  {
554  pdInstance->receivingData[0] = ((uint32_t *)pdInstance->receivingDataBuffer)[0]; /* msg header */
555  receiveLength -= 4; /* reduce the normal header and ext header */
556  for (index = 0; index < (receiveLength); ++index)
557  {
558  destBuffer[index] = sourceBuffer[index];
559  }
560  pdInstance->receivedData = (uint32_t *)&(pdInstance->receivingData[0]);
561  }
562  else
563 #endif
564  {
565  pdInstance->receivedData = (uint32_t *)pdInstance->receivingDataBuffer;
566  }
567  }
568 
569  retVal = (pdInstance->receiveResult == kStatus_PD_Success ? 1 : 0);
570  }
571 
572  return retVal;
573 }

pd_status_t PD_MsgSend ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance,
start_of_packet_t  sop,
message_type_t  msgType,
uint32_t  dataLength,
uint8_t *  dataBuffer 
)
143 {
144  uint8_t index;
145  USB_OSA_SR_ALLOC();
146 
147  USB_OSA_ENTER_CRITICAL();
148  if ((pdInstance->hardResetReceived) || (pdInstance->sendingState == 1))
149  {
150  USB_OSA_EXIT_CRITICAL();
151  return kStatus_PD_Error;
152  }
153 
154  pdInstance->sendingState = 1;
155  USB_OSA_EXIT_CRITICAL();
156 
157  /* set msg header */
158  pdInstance->sendingData[0] = (pdInstance->sendingMsgHeader.msgHeaderVal | (msgType & PD_MSG_TYPE_VALUE_MASK) |
159  (((dataLength - 2) >> 2) << PD_MSG_HEADER_NUMBER_OF_DATA_OBJECTS_POS))
160  << 16;
161  /* copy msg data */
162  if (msgType != kPD_MsgSourceCapabilities)
163  {
164  for (index = 0; index < ((dataLength - 2 + 3) >> 2); ++index)
165  {
166  pdInstance->sendingData[index + 1] = USB_LONG_FROM_LITTLE_ENDIAN_ADDRESS((dataBuffer + index * 4));
167  }
168  }
169 
170  PD_MsgReceive(pdInstance);
171  if (pdInstance->phyInterface->pdPhySend(pdInstance->pdPhyHandle, sop,
172  ((uint8_t *)&(pdInstance->sendingData[0])) + 2,
173  (dataLength)) == kStatus_PD_Success)
174  {
175  return kStatus_PD_Success;
176  }
177  else
178  {
179  pdInstance->sendingState = 0;
180  }
181 
182  return kStatus_PD_Error;
183 }

uint8_t PD_MsgWaitSendResult ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance)
116 {
117  uint32_t eventSet;
118  do
119  {
120  eventSet = 0u;
121  USB_OsaEventWait(pdInstance->taskEventHandle, 0xffu, 0, 5, &eventSet);
122  PD_PortTaskEventProcess(pdInstance, eventSet);
123  if (eventSet & PD_TASK_EVENT_SEND_DONE)
124  {
125  USB_OsaEventClear(pdInstance->taskEventHandle, PD_TASK_EVENT_SEND_DONE);
126  break;
127  }
128 
129  /* Disconnected */
130  if (PD_ConnectCheck(pdInstance) == (uint8_t)kConnectState_Disconnected)
131  {
132  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_CANCEL_MSG_TX, NULL);
133  pdInstance->sendingState = 0;
134  return kStatus_PD_Error;
135  }
136  } while (1);
137 
138  return ((pdInstance->sendingResult == kStatus_PD_Success) ? 1 : 0);
139 }

void PD_PortTaskEventProcess ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance,
uint32_t  eventSet 
)
663 {
664  // 如果phy state change, 则通过call back调用alert handler
665  // alert interrupt handler will set PD_TASK_EVENT_PHY_STATE_CHAGNE and PD_TASK_EVENT_TYPEC_STATE_PROCESS, 中断只是设置flag，而不做处理
666  if (eventSet & PD_TASK_EVENT_PHY_STATE_CHAGNE)
667  {
668  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_UPDATE_STATE, NULL);
669  }
670 
671  // Question: other event 的作用
672  if (eventSet & PD_TASK_EVENT_OTHER)
673  {
674  USB_OsaEventClear(pdInstance->taskEventHandle, PD_TASK_EVENT_OTHER);
675  }
676 
677  if (pdInstance->isConnected)
678  {
679  eventSet &= (~(PD_TASK_EVENT_PHY_STATE_CHAGNE | PD_TASK_EVENT_OTHER | PD_TASK_EVENT_FR_SWAP_SINGAL |
680  PD_TASK_EVENT_DPM_MSG));
681  }
682  else
683  {
684  eventSet &= (~(PD_TASK_EVENT_PHY_STATE_CHAGNE | PD_TASK_EVENT_OTHER | PD_TASK_EVENT_FR_SWAP_SINGAL));
685  }
686 
687  /* clear the events that aren't processed in this condition */
688  if (eventSet)
689  {
690  // 如果dpm state machine不存在
691  if (!((pdInstance->dpmStateMachine == 1) && (pdInstance->isConnected)))
692  {
693  USB_OsaEventClear(pdInstance->taskEventHandle, eventSet);
694  }
695  }
696 }

761  }
762  break;

773  }
774  break;
775  }
776  case PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET:

778  event = PD_DPM_SOFT_RESET_FAIL;
779  break;
780  }

782  {

4468  pdInstance->commandProcessing = 0;
4469  }
4470  }
4471  pdInstance->psmCapsCounter++;
4472  if (PD_MsgSendDataTransition(
4473  pdInstance, kPD_MsgSourceCapabilities, pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sourceCapCount,
4474  PD_PsmGetSourcePDOs(pdInstance), PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE, PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX,
4475  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected ? PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET : PSM_PE_SRC_DISCOVERY))
4476  {
4477  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected = 1;
4478  pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected = 1;
4479  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer);
4480  pdInstance->psmHardResetCount = 0;
4481  pdInstance->psmCapsCounter = 0;
4482  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4483  }
4484  break;
4485 
4486  case PSM_PE_SRC_NEGOTIATE_CAPABILITY: /* (C) */
4487  {
4488  pd_negotiate_power_request_t negotiateResult;
4489 
4490  if ((pdInstance->partnerRdoRequest.bitFields.unchunkedSupported) &&
4491  (pdInstance->selfOrPartnerFirstSourcePDO.fixedPDO.unchunkedSupported))
4492  {
4493  pdInstance->unchunkedFeature = 1;
4494  }
4495  else
4496  {
4497  pdInstance->unchunkedFeature = 0;
4498  }
4499 
4500  negotiateResult.rdo = pdInstance->partnerRdoRequest;
4501  negotiateResult.negotiateResult = kCommandResult_Accept;
4502  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SRC_RDO_REQUEST, &negotiateResult, 0);
4503  if (negotiateResult.negotiateResult == kCommandResult_Accept)
4504  {
4505  pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx = 0;
4506  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_SUPPLY;
4507  }
4508  else
4509  {
4510  pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult = negotiateResult.negotiateResult;
4511  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_CAPABILITY_RESPONSE;
4512  }
4513  break;
4514  }
4515 
4516  case PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_SUPPLY: /* (C) */
4517  if (pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx)
4518  {
4519  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgGotoMin;
4520  }
4521  else
4522  {
4523  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgAccept;
4524  }
4525 
4526  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, (message_type_t)inCase32Tmp, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE,
4527  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4528  {
4529  /* transition power */
4530  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tDelayTimer, T_SRC_TRANSITION);
4531  while (!PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tDelayTimer))
4532  ;
4533  if (pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx)
4534  {
4535  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcGotoMinReducePower(pdInstance->callbackParam);
4536  }
4537  else
4538  {
4539  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcTurnOnRequestVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam,
4540  pdInstance->partnerRdoRequest);
4541  }
4542  }
4543  else
4544  {
4545  if (pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx)
4546  {
4547  pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx = 0;
4548  }
4549  }
4550  break;
4551 
4552  case PSM_PE_SRC_READY: /* (C) */
4553  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[0] = PSM_IDLE;
4554  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[1] = PSM_IDLE;
4555  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[2] = PSM_IDLE;
4556  pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted = 1;
4557 /* cannot receive SOP' until explicit contract */
4558 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE)
4559  if (pdInstance->curDataRole == kPD_DataRoleDFP)
4560  {
4561  pdInstance->pendingSOP = kPD_MsgSOPMask | kPD_MsgSOPpMask | kPD_MsgSOPppMask;
4562  }
4563 #endif
4564  break;
4565 
4566  case PSM_PE_SRC_WAIT_NEW_CAPABILITIES: /* (C) */
4567  break;
4568 
4569  case PSM_PE_SRC_DISABLED: /* (C) */
4570  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_DISABLE_MSG_RX, NULL);
4571  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_FUNCTION_DISABLED, NULL, 0);
4572  break;
4573 
4574  case PSM_PE_SRC_CAPABILITY_RESPONSE: /* (C) */
4575  if (pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult == kCommandResult_Reject)
4576  {
4577  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgReject;
4578  }
4579  else
4580  {
4581  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgWait;
4582  }
4583 
4584  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, (message_type_t)inCase32Tmp, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE,
4585  PSM_HARD_RESET, PSM_HARD_RESET))
4586  {
4587  if (!pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted)
4588  {
4589  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_WAIT_NEW_CAPABILITIES;
4590  }
4591  else
4592  {
4593  uint8_t stillValid = 0;
4594  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SRC_CONTRACT_STILL_VALID, &stillValid, 0);
4595  if ((stillValid) || (inCase32Tmp == kPD_MsgWait))
4596  {
4597  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
4598  }
4599  else
4600  {
4601  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
4602  }
4603  }
4604  }
4605  break;
4606 
4607  case PSM_PE_SRC_HARD_RESET_RECEIVED: /* (C) */
4608  break;
4609 
4610  case PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT: /* (C) */
4611  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected = 0;
4612  pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted = 0u;
4613  pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V = 1;
4614 
4615  /* source send hard_reset, 2. change to supply vsafe5v. */
4616  /* source receive hard_reset, 2. change to supply vsafe5v. */
4617  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSrcRecoverTimer);
4618  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcTurnOffVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InHardReset);
4619  PD_DpmDischargeVbus(pdInstance, 1);
4620  while (!PD_DpmCheckVsafe0V(pdInstance))
4621  {
4622  }
4623  PD_DpmDischargeVbus(pdInstance, 0);
4624  /* source send hard_reset, 3. start tSrcRecover timer. */
4625  /* source receive hard_reset, 3. start tSrcRecover timer. */
4626  /* 1. vbus is vsafe0v -> start the tSrcRecover timer -> After tSrcRecover the Source applies power to
4627  * VBUS */
4628  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSrcRecoverTimer, T_SRC_RECOVER);
4629 
4630  /* Message reception should not be re-enabled until PE_SNK_Startup */
4631  PD_MsgReset(pdInstance);
4632  /* Change our data role to DFP, and turn off vconn */
4633  pdInstance->curDataRole = kPD_DataRoleDFP;
4634  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
4635 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT)
4636  /* Request DPM to turn off vconn */
4637  PD_DpmSetVconn(pdInstance, 0);
4638 #ifdef USBPD_ENABLE_VCONN_DISCHARGE
4639  PD_DpmDischargeVconn(pdInstance, 1);
4640 #endif
4641 #endif
4642  break;
4643 
4644  case PSM_PE_SRC_GIVE_SOURCE_CAP: /* (C) */
4645  if (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sourceCaps != NULL)
4646  {
4647  PD_MsgSendDataTransition(
4648  pdInstance, kPD_MsgSourceCapabilities, pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sourceCapCount,
4649  PD_PsmGetSourcePDOs(pdInstance), PSM_PE_SRC_READY, PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4650  }
4651  else
4652  {
4653  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, PD_NOT_SUPPORT_REPLY_MSG, PSM_PE_SRC_READY);
4654  }
4655  break;
4656 #endif
4657 
4658 #if ((defined PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE)) || \
4659  (defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE))
4660 
4661 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE)
4662  case PSM_PE_SRC_GET_SINK_CAP: /* (C) */
4663 #endif
4664 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
4665  case PSM_PE_DR_SNK_GET_SINK_CAP: /* (C) */
4666 #endif
4667  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgGetSinkCap, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE, prevState,
4668  PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4669  {
4670  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4671  }
4672  break;
4673 #endif
4674 
4675 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
4676  case PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GET_SOURCE_CAP: /* (C) */
4677  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgGetSourceCap, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE, prevState,
4678  PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4679  {
4680  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4681  }
4682  break;
4683 #endif
4684 
4685 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE)
4686  case PSM_PE_SNK_GET_SOURCE_CAP: /* (C) */
4687  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgGetSourceCap, PSM_PE_SNK_READY, prevState,
4688  PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4689  {
4690  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4691  }
4692  break;
4693 #endif
4694 
4695 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
4696  case PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GIVE_SINK_CAP: /* (C) */
4697  if ((pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->typecRole != kPowerConfig_SourceOnly) &&
4698  (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCaps != NULL))
4699  {
4700  PD_MsgSendDataTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgSinkCapabilities,
4701  pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCapCount,
4702  pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCaps, PSM_PE_SRC_READY,
4703  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4704  }
4705  else
4706  {
4707  PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, PD_NOT_SUPPORT_REPLY_MSG, PSM_PE_SRC_READY,
4708  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4709  }
4710  break;
4711 
4712  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_EVALUATE_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4713  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_PR_SWAP_REQUEST, &pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult, 0);
4714  if (pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult == kCommandResult_Accept)
4715  {
4716  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_ACCEPT_PR_SWAP;
4717  }
4718  else
4719  {
4720  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_REJECT_PR_SWAP;
4721  }
4722  break;
4723 
4724  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_ACCEPT_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4725  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, kPD_MsgAccept, PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_OFF);
4726  break;
4727 
4728  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_OFF: /* (C) */
4729  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_InPRSwap);
4730 
4731  /* pr swap transition to standby */
4732  /* 1. tSrcTransition */
4733  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tDelayTimer, T_SRC_TRANSITION);
4734  while (!PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tDelayTimer))
4735  ;
4736  /* 2. start enter to standby tSrcSwapStdby */
4737  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcTurnOffVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InPRSwap);
4738  PD_DpmDischargeVbus(pdInstance, 1);
4739  break;
4740 
4741  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_ASSERT_RD: /* (C) */
4742  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSink;
4743  PD_ConnectSetPRSwapRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole);
4744  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_WAIT_SOURCE_ON;
4745  break;
4746 
4747  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_WAIT_SOURCE_ON: /* (C) */
4748  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSink;
4749  /* 0 Role stays as standby until we receive the PS_RDY message */
4750  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
4751  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgPsRdy, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE,
4752  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY,
4753  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY))
4754  {
4755  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSSourceOnTimer, T_PS_SOURCE_ON);
4756  }
4757  break;
4758 
4759  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_SEND_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4760  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgPrSwap, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE, prevState,
4761  PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4762  {
4763  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4764  }
4765  break;
4766 
4767  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_REJECT_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4768  if (pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult == kCommandResult_Reject)
4769  {
4770  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgReject;
4771  }
4772  else
4773  {
4774  inCase32Tmp = kPD_MsgWait;
4775  }
4776  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, inCase32Tmp, PSM_PE_SRC_READY);
4777  break;
4778 #endif
4779 
4780 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE)
4781  case PSM_PE_SNK_STARTUP: /* (C) */
4782  /* Delay for 1ms to make sure any previous GoodCRC tranmission has ended. */
4783  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tDelayTimer, mSec(1));
4784  while (!(PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tDelayTimer)))
4785  {
4786  ;
4787  }
4788  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
4789 
4790  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected = 0;
4791  /* Do not clear previouslyPdConnected here */
4792  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_DISCOVERY;
4793  break;
4794 
4795  case PSM_PE_SNK_DISCOVERY: /* (C) */
4796  break;
4797 
4798  case PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES: /* (C) */
4799  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
4800  PD_MsgStartReceive(pdInstance);
4801  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSinkWaitCapTimer, T_SINK_WAIT_CAP);
4802  break;
4803 
4804  case PSM_PE_SNK_EVALUATE_CAPABILITY: /* (C) */
4805  pdInstance->psmHardResetCount = 0;
4806  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer);
4807  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SNK_GET_RDO, &pdInstance->rdoRequest, 0);
4808  if (pdInstance->commandProcessing == 0)
4809  {
4810  PD_PsmStartCommand(pdInstance, PD_DPM_CONTROL_REQUEST, 0);
4811  }
4812  if ((pdInstance->rdoRequest.bitFields.unchunkedSupported) &&
4813  (pdInstance->selfOrPartnerFirstSourcePDO.fixedPDO.unchunkedSupported))
4814  {
4815  pdInstance->unchunkedFeature = 1;
4816  }
4817  else
4818  {
4819  pdInstance->unchunkedFeature = 0;
4820  }
4821  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY;
4822  break;
4823 
4824  case PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY: /* (C) */
4825  /* TX interrupted by RX */
4826  if (prevState == PSM_PE_SNK_READY)
4827  {
4828  inCase32Tmp = prevState;
4829  }
4830  else
4831  {
4832  /* receive packet */
4833  inCase32Tmp = PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX;
4834  }
4835 
4836  if (PD_MsgSendDataTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgRequest, 1, (uint32_t *)(&pdInstance->rdoRequest),
4837  PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE, inCase32Tmp, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
4838  {
4839  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
4840  }
4841  break;
4842 
4843  case PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY_WAIT_TIMER_TIME_OUT: /* (C) */
4844  break;
4845 
4846  case PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_SINK: /* (C) */
4847  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSTransitionTimer, T_PS_TRANSITION);
4848  if (pdInstance->psmGotoMinRx)
4849  {
4850  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkGotoMinReducePower(pdInstance->callbackParam);
4851  }
4852  else
4853  {
4854  /* Start ignoring droops on VBus */
4855  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_ChangeInProgress);
4856  }
4857  break;
4858 
4859  case PSM_PE_SNK_READY: /* (C) */
4860  inCase32Tmp = 1;
4861  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[0] = PSM_IDLE;
4862  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[1] = PSM_IDLE;
4863  pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[2] = PSM_IDLE;
4864  pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted = 1;
4865 /* cannot receive SOP' until explicit contract */
4866 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE)
4867  if (pdInstance->curDataRole == kPD_DataRoleDFP)
4868  {
4869  pdInstance->pendingSOP = kPD_MsgSOPMask | kPD_MsgSOPpMask | kPD_MsgSOPppMask;
4870  }
4871 #endif
4872 
4873  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_CONTROL_FR_SWAP, &inCase32Tmp);
4874 
4875  /* Stop ignoring droops on VBus */
4876  /* kVbusPower_ChangeInProgress is done */
4877  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
4878  break;
4879 
4880  case PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT: /* (C) */
4881  /* Message reception should not be re-enabled until PE_SNK_Startup */
4882  PD_MsgReset(pdInstance);
4883  pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted = 0u;
4884  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected = 0;
4885  pdInstance->curDataRole = kPD_DataRoleUFP;
4886  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
4887 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT)
4888  /* Request DPM to turn off vconn */
4889  PD_DpmSetVconn(pdInstance, 0);
4890 #endif
4891 
4892  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer, T_NO_RESPONSE);
4893  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_GET_VBUS_POWER_STATE, &inCase32Tmp);
4894  if (!(inCase32Tmp & PD_VBUS_POWER_STATE_VSAFE0V_MASK))
4895  {
4896  pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V = 1;
4897  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSHardResetTimer, T_PS_HARD_RESET + 10);
4898  }
4899  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_STARTUP;
4900  break;
4901 
4902  case PSM_PE_SNK_GIVE_SINK_CAP: /* (C) */
4903  if (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCaps != NULL)
4904  {
4905  PD_MsgSendDataTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgSinkCapabilities,
4906  pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCapCount,
4907  pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sinkCaps, PSM_PE_SNK_READY,
4908  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4909  }
4910  else
4911  {
4912  PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, PD_NOT_SUPPORT_REPLY_MSG, PSM_PE_SNK_READY,
4913  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4914  }
4915  break;
4916 #endif
4917 
4918 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
4919  case PSM_PE_DR_SNK_GIVE_SOURCE_CAP: /* (C) */
4920  if (((pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->typecRole == kPowerConfig_SourceOnly) ||
4921  (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->typecRole == kPowerConfig_SinkDefault) ||
4922  (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->typecRole == kPowerConfig_DRPToggling)) &&
4923  (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sourceCaps != NULL))
4924  {
4925  PD_MsgSendDataTransition(
4926  pdInstance, kPD_MsgSourceCapabilities, pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->sourceCapCount,
4927  PD_PsmGetSourcePDOs(pdInstance), PSM_PE_SNK_READY, PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4928  }
4929  else
4930  {
4931  PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, PD_NOT_SUPPORT_REPLY_MSG, PSM_PE_SNK_READY,
4932  PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
4933  }
4934  break;
4935 
4936  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_EVALUATE_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4937  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_PR_SWAP_REQUEST, &pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult, 0);
4938  if (pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult == kCommandResult_Accept)
4939  {
4940  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_ACCEPT_PR_SWAP;
4941  }
4942  else
4943  {
4944  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_REJECT_PR_SWAP;
4945  }
4946  break;
4947 
4948  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_ACCEPT_PR_SWAP: /* (C) */
4949  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, kPD_MsgAccept, PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_OFF);
4950  break;
4951 
4952  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_OFF: /* (C) */
4953  pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted = 0;
4954  inCase32Tmp = 0u;
4955  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_CONTROL_FR_SWAP, &inCase32Tmp);
4956  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSSourceOffTimer, T_PS_SOURCE_OFF);
4957  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_InPRSwap);
4958  /* sink transition to standby. */
4959  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkStopDrawVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InPRSwap);
4960  break;
4961 
4962  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_ASSERT_RP: /* (C) */
4963  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSource;
4964  /* We must assume a new default role */
4965  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSource;

5467  else
5468  {
5469  sendStatus = PD_MsgSendDefaultControl(pdInstance, kPD_MsgNotSupported);
5470  }
5471  }
5472  else
5473  {
5474  extHeader.bitFields.requestChunk = 0;
5475  sendLength = (pdInstance->extAllDataSize - (extHeader.bitFields.chunkNumber * 26));
5476  if (sendLength > 26)
5477  {
5478  sendLength = 26;
5479  }
5480  sendStatus = PD_MsgSendChunkedExtendedMsg(
5481  pdInstance, (start_of_packet_t)pdInstance->commandExtParam.sop, kPD_MsgSecurityRequest, extHeader,
5482  sendLength, (pdInstance->extDataBuffer + extHeader.bitFields.chunkNumber * 26));
5483  }
5484 
5485  if ((sendStatus == kStatus_PD_Success) && (PD_MsgWaitSendResult(pdInstance)))
5486  {
5487  if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSink)
5488  {
5489  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
5490  }
5491  else
5492  {
5493  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
5494  }
5495  }
5496  else
5497  {
5498  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendError(pdInstance, PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET);
5499  }
5500  break;
5501  }
5502 
5503  case PE_Security_Response_Received: /* C */
5504  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SECURITY_RESPONSE_RECEIVED, &pdInstance->commandExtParamCallback, 0);
5505  if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSink)
5506  {
5507  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
5508  }
5509  else
5510  {
5511  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
5512  }
5513  break;
5514 #endif
5515 
5516  case PE_SRC_Send_Source_Alert: /* C */
5517  case PE_SNK_Send_Sink_Alert: /* C */
5518  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PE_SNK_Send_Sink_Alert)
5519  {
5520  inCase32Tmp = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
5521  }
5522  else
5523  {
5524  inCase32Tmp = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
5525  }
5526 
5527  if (PD_MsgSendDataTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgAlert, 1, &pdInstance->alertADO,
5528  (pd_psm_state_t)inCase32Tmp, prevState, PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET))
5529  {
5530  pdInstance->alertWaitReply = 1u;
5531  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SEND_ALERT_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
5532  }
5533  else
5534  {
5535  inCase32Tmp = kCommandResult_Error;
5536  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SEND_ALERT_FAIL, &inCase32Tmp, 1);
5537  }
5538  break;
5539 
5540  case PE_SNK_Source_Alert_Received: /* C */
5541  case PE_SRC_Sink_Alert_Received: /* C */
5542  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PE_SNK_Source_Alert_Received)
5543  {
5544  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
5545  }
5546  else
5547  {
5548  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
5549  }
5550  break;
5551 #endif
5552 
5553 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_PD3_FAST_ROLE_SWAP_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_PD3_FAST_ROLE_SWAP_ENABLE)
5554  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_CC_Signal: /* C */
5555  {
5556  PD_MsgReceive(pdInstance);
5557  break;
5558  }
5559 
5560  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Evaluate_Swap: /* C */
5561  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_FR_SWAP_REQUEST, &pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult, 0);
5562  if (pdInstance->commandEvaluateResult == kCommandResult_Accept)
5563  {
5564  pdInstance->psmNewState = PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Accept_Swap;
5565  }
5566  else
5567  {
5568  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
5569  }
5570  break;
5571 
5572  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Accept_Swap: /* C */
5573  PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgAccept, PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Transition_to_off, PSM_HARD_RESET,
5574  PSM_HARD_RESET);
5575  break;
5576 
5577  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Transition_to_off: /* C */
5578  break;
5579 
5580  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Assert_Rd: /* C */
5581  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSink;
5582  PD_ConnectSetPRSwapRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole);
5583  pdInstance->psmNewState = PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Wait_Source_on;
5584  break;
5585 
5586  case PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_Wait_Source_on: /* C */
5587  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
5588  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgPsRdy, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE,
5589  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY, PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY))
5590  {
5591  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSSourceOnTimer, T_PS_SOURCE_ON);
5592  }
5593  break;
5594 
5595  case PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Send_Swap: /* C */
5596  inCase32Tmp = 0;
5597  pdInstance->fr5VOpened = 0;
5598  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_CONTROL_FR_SWAP, &inCase32Tmp);
5599  if ((pdInstance->fr5VOpened == 0) && PD_DpmCheckLessOrEqualVsafe5v(pdInstance))
5600  {
5601  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcTurnOnTypeCVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InFRSwap);
5602  pdInstance->fr5VOpened = 1;
5603  }
5604  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgFrSwap, PE_PSM_STATE_NO_CHANGE,
5605  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY,
5606  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY))
5607  {
5608  PD_PsmStartCommand(pdInstance, PD_DPM_FAST_ROLE_SWAP, 0);
5609  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer, T_SENDER_RESPONSE);
5610  }
5611  else
5612  {
5613  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY;
5614  }
5615  break;
5616 
5617  case PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Transition_to_off: /* C */
5618  /* uint8_t enable = 0; */
5619  /* PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_CONTROL_FR_SWAP, &enable); */
5620  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSSourceOffTimer, T_PS_SOURCE_OFF);
5621  break;
5622 
5623  case PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Vbus_Applied: /* C */
5624  break;
5625 
5626  case PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Assert_Rp: /* C */
5627  pdInstance->curPowerRole = kPD_PowerRoleSource;
5628  PD_ConnectSetPRSwapRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole);
5629  pdInstance->psmNewState = PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Source_on;
5630  break;
5631 
5632  case PE_FRS_SNK_SRC_Source_on: /* C */
5633  if (PD_MsgSendControlTransition(pdInstance, kPD_MsgPsRdy, PSM_PE_SRC_STARTUP,
5634  PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY, PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY))
5635  {
5636  /* pr swap end */
5637  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
5638 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE)
5639  /* Cable plug will need a soft reset */
5640  pdInstance->psmCablePlugResetNeeded = 1;
5641 #endif
5642  pdInstance->enterSrcFromSwap = 1;
5643  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_FR_SWAP_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
5644  }
5645  break;
5646 #endif
5647 
5648  default:
5649  break;
5650  }
5651 
5652  PD_PsmEndCommand(pdInstance, pdInstance->psmCurState);
5653  PD_PsmSetNormalPower(pdInstance, pdInstance->psmCurState);
5654  }
5655 
5656  if (didNothingC == 1)
5657  {
5658  return kSM_WaitEvent;
5659  }
5660  else
5661  {
5662  return kSM_Continue;
5663  }
5664 }

static uint8_t PD_PsmPrimaryStateProcessDpmMsg ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance,
uint8_t *  returnNewState,
psm_trigger_info_t *  triggerInfo 
)
static
366 {
367  uint8_t newStateTmp = PSM_UNKNOWN;
368  uint8_t didNothing = 1;
369 
370  /* assume the message is processed */
371  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NONE;
372  switch (triggerInfo->dpmMsg)
373  {
374  case PD_DPM_CONTROL_HARD_RESET:
375  newStateTmp = PSM_HARD_RESET;
376  didNothing = 0;
377  break;
378 
379  case PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET:
380  if (PD_PsmStartCommand(pdInstance, PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET, 1))
381  {
382  newStateTmp = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
383  didNothing = 0;
384  }
385  else
386  {
387  PD_PsmCommandFail(pdInstance, PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET);
388  }
389  break;
390 #if 0
391  case PD_DPM_CONTROL_EXIT_MODE:
392  pdInstance->vdmExitReceived[pdInstance->structuredVdmCommandParameter.vdmSop] = 1;
393  break;
394 #endif
395 
396 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_PD3_FAST_ROLE_SWAP_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_PD3_FAST_ROLE_SWAP_ENABLE)
397  case PD_DPM_FAST_ROLE_SWAP:
398  if (PD_PsmStartCommand(pdInstance, PD_DPM_FAST_ROLE_SWAP, 1))
399  {
400  pdInstance->psmNewState = PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_CC_Signal;
401  }
402  break;
403 #endif
404 
405  default:
406  /* the event is not processed */
407  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_DPM_MSG;
408  break;
409  }
410 
411  if (newStateTmp != PSM_UNKNOWN)
412  {
413  *returnNewState = newStateTmp;
414  }
415 
416  return didNothing;
417 }

static uint8_t PD_PsmPrimaryStateProcessPdMsg ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance,
uint8_t *  returnNewState,
psm_trigger_info_t *  triggerInfo 
)
static
422 {
423  uint8_t newStateTmp = PSM_UNKNOWN;
424  uint8_t didNothing = 1;
425 
426  if (triggerInfo->triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_RECEIVE_HARD_RESET)
427  {
428  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NONE;
429 
430  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PSM_PE_BIST_TEST_DATA_MODE)
431  {
432  /* From the IAS: There is no exit from this test mode except some chip level reset.
433  Reset the protocol layer to exit carrier mode */
434  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_EXIT_BIST, NULL);
435  }
436  /* Exit any active alternate mode */
437  /* All timers and secondary states are reset during this call */
438  PD_PsmReset(pdInstance);
439 
440  if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSource)
441  {
442  /* source receive hard_reset, 1. start tPSHardReset */
443  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPSHardResetTimer, T_PS_HARD_RESET);
444  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_SRC_HARD_RESET_RECEIVED;
445  }
446  else if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSink)
447  {
448  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkStopDrawVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InHardReset);
449  pdInstance->asmHardResetSnkProcessing = 1;
450  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT;
451  }
452  else
453  {
454  }
455  didNothing = 0;
456  }
457  else if ((triggerInfo->triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG) && (triggerInfo->pdMsgType == kPD_MsgBIST))
458  {
459 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_COMPLIANCE_TEST_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_COMPLIANCE_TEST_ENABLE)
460  pd_bist_object_t bistObj;
461  bistObj.objVal = USB_LONG_FROM_LITTLE_ENDIAN_ADDRESS(triggerInfo->pdMsgDataBuffer);
462  if (bistObj.bitFields.testMode == kBIST_TestData)
463  {
464  /* Do nothing, the HW does not have a mode for kBIST_TestData */
465  newStateTmp = kBIST_TestData;
466  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_ENTER_BIST, &newStateTmp);
467  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_BIST_TEST_DATA_MODE;
468  }
469  else
470  {
471  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer);
472  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_BIST_CARRIER_MODE_2;
473  }
474 #endif
475  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NONE;
476  }
477  else if ((triggerInfo->triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG) && (triggerInfo->pdMsgType == kPD_MsgSoftReset))
478  {
479  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NONE;
480  /* Soft reset is ignored when in BIST carrier mode */
481  /* Soft reset is ignored during fast role swap signalling */
482  if ((pdInstance->psmCurState != PSM_PE_BIST_CARRIER_MODE_2) &&
483  (pdInstance->psmCurState != PE_FRS_SRC_SNK_CC_Signal))
484  {
485  PD_PsmStartCommand(pdInstance, PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET, 0);
486  newStateTmp = PSM_SOFT_RESET;
487  didNothing = 0;
488  }
489  }
490  /* The received message's data role is not right */
491  else if ((pdInstance->curDataRole == triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.portDataRole) &&
492  (triggerInfo->pdMsgType != kPD_MsgGoodCRC))
493  {
494  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NON_START;
495  newStateTmp = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY;
496  didNothing = 0;
497  }
498  /* received source_capabilities */
499  else if ((pdInstance->psmCurState != PSM_PE_SNK_DISCOVERY) && (triggerInfo->pdMsgType == kPD_MsgSourceCapabilities))
500  {
501  uint32_t u32Tmp = 0;
502 
503  (void)u32Tmp;
504  triggerInfo->triggerEvent = PSM_TRIGGER_NONE;
505  if (pdInstance->pdPowerPortConfig->typecRole == kPowerConfig_SourceOnly)
506  {
507  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, PD_NOT_SUPPORT_REPLY_MSG, pdInstance->psmCurState);
508  }
509  else
510  {
511  switch (pdInstance->psmCurState)
512  {
513 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE)
514  case PSM_PE_SRC_DISCOVERY:
515  case PSM_PE_SRC_SEND_CAPABILITIES:
516  case PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_SUPPLY:
517  case PSM_PE_SRC_READY:
518  case PSM_PE_SRC_GET_SINK_CAP:
519 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE)
520  if ((pdInstance->curDataRole == triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.portDataRole) &&
521  (triggerInfo->pdMsgType != kPD_MsgGoodCRC))
522  {
523  /* Conflicting data roles (with delay for good crc tx) */
524  newStateTmp = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY;
525  }
526  else
527 #endif
528  {
529  newStateTmp = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
530  }
531  break;
532 
533 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
534  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_OFF:
535  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_WAIT_SOURCE_ON:
536  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_SEND_PR_SWAP:
537  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_SOURCE_ON:
538 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE)
539  if ((pdInstance->curDataRole == triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.portDataRole) &&
540  (triggerInfo->pdMsgType != kPD_MsgGoodCRC))
541  {
542  /* Conflicting data roles (with delay for good crc tx) */
543  newStateTmp = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY;
544  }
545  else
546 #endif
547  {
548  /* A protocol error during power role swap triggers a Hard Reset */
549  newStateTmp = PSM_HARD_RESET;
550  }
551  break;
552 #endif
553 
554 #endif
555 
556 /* Source state, message expected */
557 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
558  case PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GET_SOURCE_CAP:
559  case PSM_PE_SNK_GET_SOURCE_CAP:
560  {
561  pd_capabilities_t sourceCapa;
562  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer);
563  /* Clear any pending message now that we have the latest */
564  (void)PD_DpmClearMsg(pdInstance, PD_DPM_CONTROL_GET_PARTNER_SOURCE_CAPABILITIES);
565  sourceCapa.capabilities = MSG_DATA_BUFFER;
566  sourceCapa.capabilitiesCount = (triggerInfo->pdMsgDataLength);
567  if (pdInstance->commandProcessing == PD_DPM_CONTROL_GET_PARTNER_SOURCE_CAPABILITIES)
568  {
569  pdInstance->commandProcessing = 0;
570  }
571  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_GET_PARTNER_SRC_CAP_SUCCESS, &sourceCapa, 1);
572  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PSM_PE_SNK_GET_SOURCE_CAP)
573  {
574  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
575  }
576  else
577  {
578  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
579  }
580  break;
581  }
582 #endif
583 
584 /* Sink states, message accepted: */
585 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE)
586  case PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES:
587  case PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY:
588  case PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_SINK:
589  case PSM_PE_SNK_READY:
590  case PSM_PE_SNK_GIVE_SINK_CAP:
591 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
592  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_OFF:
593  case PSM_PE_PRS_SNK_SRC_SEND_PR_SWAP:
594  case PSM_PE_DR_SNK_GET_SINK_CAP:
595 #endif
596 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_DATA_ROLE_ENABLE)
597  if ((pdInstance->curDataRole == triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.portDataRole) &&
598  (triggerInfo->pdMsgType != kPD_MsgGoodCRC))
599  {
600  /* Conflicting data roles (with delay for good crc tx) */
601  newStateTmp = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY;
602  }
603  else
604 #endif
605  {
606  pd_capabilities_t sourceCapa;
607  if (pdInstance->revision > triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.specRevision)
608  {
609  pdInstance->revision = triggerInfo->msgHeader.bitFields.specRevision;
610  PD_MsgSetPortRole(pdInstance, pdInstance->curPowerRole, pdInstance->curDataRole);
611  }
612  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSinkWaitCapTimer);
613  pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected = 1;
614  pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected = 1;
615 
616  /* Update the PDOs for the EC and send interrupt */
617  sourceCapa.capabilities = MSG_DATA_BUFFER;
618  sourceCapa.capabilitiesCount = (triggerInfo->pdMsgDataLength);
619  pdInstance->selfOrPartnerFirstSourcePDO.PDOValue = sourceCapa.capabilities[0];
620  if (pdInstance->commandProcessing == PD_DPM_CONTROL_GET_PARTNER_SOURCE_CAPABILITIES)
621  {
622  pdInstance->commandProcessing = 0;
623  }
624  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SNK_RECEIVE_PARTNER_SRC_CAP, &sourceCapa, 0);
625 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE)
626  /* Ensure secondary state machine does not transition primary state machine */
627  PD_PsmSecondaryStateHandlerTerminate(pdInstance, 0xffu);
628 #endif
629  newStateTmp = PSM_PE_SNK_EVALUATE_CAPABILITY;
630  }
631  break;
632 #endif
633 
634  default:
635  break;
636  }
637  }
638 
639  didNothing = 0;
640  }
641 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE)
642  else if ((triggerInfo->triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG) && (triggerInfo->pdMsgType == kPD_MsgVendorDefined) &&
643  (triggerInfo->vdmHeader.bitFields.command == kVDM_ExitMode) &&
644  (triggerInfo->vdmHeader.bitFields.commandType == kVDM_Initiator))
645  {
646  pdInstance->vdmExitReceived[triggerInfo->pdMsgSop] = triggerInfo->vdmHeader.bitFields.objPos;
647  }
648 #endif
649  else
650  {
651  }
652 
653  if (newStateTmp != PSM_UNKNOWN)
654  {
655  *returnNewState = newStateTmp;
656  }
657 
658  return didNothing;
659 }

2576  {
2577  didNothingStepA &=
2578  PD_PsmPrimaryStateProcessPdMsg(pdInstance, (uint8_t *)&pdInstance->psmNewState, &triggerInfo);
2579  }
2580  else if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_DPM_MSG)
2581  {
2582  didNothingStepA &=
2583  PD_PsmPrimaryStateProcessDpmMsg(pdInstance, (uint8_t *)&pdInstance->psmNewState, &triggerInfo);
2584  }
2585  else
2586  {
2587  }
2588 
2589  if (!didNothingStepA)
2590  {
2591  if ((msgReceived) && (PD_PsmCanPendingReceive(pdInstance)))
2592  {
2593  PD_MsgReceive(pdInstance); /* msg has been processed, receiving next msg */
2594  }
2595  return kSM_Continue;
2596  }
2597 
2598  /* different timeout need hard_reset */
2599  if ((PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tSinkWaitCapTimer) ||
2600  PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSTransitionTimer) ||
2601  PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer)) &&
2602  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount <= N_HARD_RESET_COUNT) && (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSink))
2603  {
2604  if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tSinkWaitCapTimer))
2605  {
2606  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSinkWaitCapTimer);
2607  }
2608 
2609  if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSTransitionTimer))
2610  {
2611  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tPSTransitionTimer);
2612  }
2613 
2614  if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer))
2615  {
2616  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer);
2617  }
2618 
2619  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2620  didNothingStepA = 0;
2621  }
2622 
2623  /* alternate mode tAMETimeoutTimer */
2624  else if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tAMETimeoutTimer))
2625  {
2626  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tAMETimeoutTimer);
2627  PD_ConnectAltModeEnterFail(pdInstance, pdInstance->psmPresentlyPdConnected);
2628 
2629 #ifdef USBPD_ENABLE_USB_BILLBOARD
2630  UsbbSetAltModeConfigResult(AMR_CONFIG_FAILED);
2631 #endif
2632  }
2633 
2634  /* Check if we are waiting for an event for state transition */
2635  else if (pdInstance->psmNewState == pdInstance->psmCurState)
2636  {
2637  didNothingStepB = 0;
2638  switch (pdInstance->psmCurState)
2639  {
2640  case PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY: /* (B) */
2641  case PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY: /* (B) */
2642  if (pdInstance->psmNewState == PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY_WITH_DELAY)
2643  {
2644  /* Delay for 1ms to make sure any previous GoodCRC transmission has ended. */
2645  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tDelayTimer, mSec(1));
2646  while (!(PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tDelayTimer)))
2647  {
2648  ;
2649  }
2650  }
2651  PD_DpmDisconnect(pdInstance);
2652  /* Exit to CLP in disconnected state */
2653  return kSM_ErrorRecovery;
2654  break;
2655 
2656 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE)
2657  case PSM_INTERRUPTED_REQUEST: /* (B) */
2658  /* Transitioned back here after VDM handling, re attempt the request */
2659  pdInstance->psmNewState = pdInstance->psmInterruptedState;
2660  pdInstance->psmInterruptedState = PSM_UNKNOWN;
2661  break;
2662 #endif
2663 
2664  /* do har_reset actively do in (C) */
2665  case PSM_HARD_RESET: /* (B) */
2666  if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSource)
2667  {
2668  /* source send hard_reset, 2. after tpstimer. */
2669  if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSHardResetTimer))
2670  {
2671  /* Hard reset is complete */
2672  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT;
2673  }
2674  else
2675  {
2676  didNothingStepB = 1;
2677  }
2678  }
2679  else if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSink)
2680  {
2681  /* sink send hard_reset */
2682  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkStopDrawVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam, kVbusPower_InHardReset);
2683  pdInstance->asmHardResetSnkProcessing = 1;
2684  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT;
2685  }
2686  else
2687  {
2688  }
2689  break;
2690 
2691  case PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET: /* (B) */
2692  if ((triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG) && (triggerInfo.pdMsgSop == kPD_MsgSOP) &&
2693  (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgAccept))
2694  {
2695  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer);
2696  if (pdInstance->commandProcessing == PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET)
2697  {
2698  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SOFT_RESET_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
2699  }
2700  else
2701  {
2702  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SOFT_RESET_REQUEST, NULL, 0);
2703  }
2704 
2705  if (pdInstance->curPowerRole == kPD_PowerRoleSource)
2706  {
2707  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_IMPLICIT_CABLE_DISCOVERY;
2708  }
2709  else
2710  {
2711  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES;
2712  }
2713  }
2714  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer))
2715  {
2716  if (pdInstance->commandProcessing == PD_DPM_CONTROL_SOFT_RESET)
2717  {
2718  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SOFT_RESET_FAIL, NULL, 1);
2719  }
2720  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2721  }
2722  else
2723  {
2724  didNothingStepB = 1;
2725  }
2726  break;
2727 
2728  case PSM_SOFT_RESET: /* (B) */
2729  /* If we get here, then recover with a hard reset */
2730  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2731  break;
2732 
2733  case PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX: /* (B) */
2734  /* The async conditions at the top of the loop have been evaluated */
2735  /* continue to soft reset */
2736  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
2737  break;
2738 
2739  case PSM_BYPASS: /* (B) */
2740  /* We do nothing here. */
2741  didNothingStepB = 1;
2742  break;
2743 
2744 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SOURCE_ROLE_ENABLE)
2745  case PSM_PE_SRC_STARTUP: /* (B) */
2746  /* only for pr_swap, the state will enter this */
2747  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
2748  {
2749  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2750  }
2751  else if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tSwapSourceStartTimer))
2752  {
2753  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSwapSourceStartTimer);
2754  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_IMPLICIT_CABLE_DISCOVERY;
2755  }
2756  else
2757  {
2758  didNothingStepB = 1;
2759  }
2760  break;
2761 
2762  case PSM_PE_SRC_DISCOVERY: /* (B) */
2763  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
2764  {
2765  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2766  }
2767  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSourceCapabilityTimer))
2768  {
2769  if ((pdInstance->psmCapsCounter > N_CAPS_COUNT))
2770  {
2771  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_DISABLED;
2772  }
2773  else
2774  {
2775  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_SEND_CAPABILITIES;
2776  }
2777  }
2778  else if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer) &&
2779  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount > N_HARD_RESET_COUNT))
2780  {
2781  if (pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected)
2782  {
2783  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
2784  }
2785  else
2786  {
2787  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_DISABLED;
2788  }
2789  }
2790  else
2791  {
2792  didNothingStepB = 1;
2793  }
2794  break;
2795 
2796  case PSM_PE_SRC_IMPLICIT_CABLE_DISCOVERY: /* (B) */
2797 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE)
2798  Pd_PsmSecondaryStateHandler(pdInstance, 1, kPD_MsgSOPp, &triggerInfo);
2799  if (pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[1] == PSM_IDLE)
2800  {
2801  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_SEND_CAPABILITIES;
2802  }
2803 #endif
2804  break;
2805 
2806  case PSM_PE_SRC_SEND_CAPABILITIES: /* (B) */
2807  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
2808  {
2809  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer);
2810  if (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgRequest)
2811  {
2812  pdInstance->partnerRdoRequest.rdoVal = *((uint32_t *)(&(triggerInfo.pdMsgDataBuffer[0])));
2813  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_NEGOTIATE_CAPABILITY;
2814  }
2815  else
2816  {
2817  /* discard vendor defined message at here */
2818  if (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgVendorDefined)
2819  {
2820  pdInstance->psmNewState = pdInstance->psmCurState;
2821  }
2822  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
2823  }
2824  }
2825  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer))
2826  {
2827  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
2828  }
2829  else if (PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer) &&
2830  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount > N_HARD_RESET_COUNT))
2831  {
2832  if (pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected)
2833  {
2834  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
2835  }
2836  else
2837  {
2838  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_DISABLED;
2839  }
2840  }
2841  else
2842  {
2843  didNothingStepB = 1;
2844  }
2845  break;
2846 
2847  case PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_SUPPLY: /* (B) */
2848  PD_PsmTransitionOnMsgSendControl(pdInstance, kPD_MsgPsRdy, PSM_PE_SRC_READY);
2849  if (pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx)
2850  {
2851  pdInstance->psmGotoMinTx = 0;
2852  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SRC_GOTOMIN_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
2853  }
2854  else
2855  {
2856  if (pdInstance->psmNewState == PSM_PE_SRC_READY)
2857  {
2858  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SRC_RDO_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
2859  }
2860  }
2861  break;
2862 
2863  case PSM_PE_SRC_READY: /* (B) */
2864  /* state machine */
2865 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE)
2866  inCase32Tmp = 1;
2867  inCase32Tmp &= Pd_PsmSecondaryStateHandler(pdInstance, 0, kPD_MsgSOP, &triggerInfo);
2868  inCase32Tmp &= Pd_PsmSecondaryStateHandler(pdInstance, 1, kPD_MsgSOPp, &triggerInfo);
2869  inCase32Tmp &= Pd_PsmSecondaryStateHandler(pdInstance, 2, kPD_MsgSOPpp, &triggerInfo);
2870  if ((pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[0] != PSM_IDLE) ||
2871  (pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[1] != PSM_IDLE) ||
2872  (pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[2] != PSM_IDLE))
2873  {
2874  if (inCase32Tmp)
2875  {
2876  didNothingStepB = 0;
2877  }
2878  break;
2879  }
2880 #endif
2881 
2882  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
2883  {
2884  didNothingStepB = 0;
2885  PD_PsmSourceRdyProcessPdMessage(pdInstance, &triggerInfo);
2886  }
2887  else if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_DPM_MSG)
2888  {
2889  didNothingStepB = 0;
2890  PD_PsmSourceRdyProcessDpmMessage(pdInstance, &triggerInfo);
2891  }
2892  else
2893  {
2894  didNothingStepB = 1;
2895  }
2896  break;
2897 
2898  case PSM_PE_SRC_DISABLED: /* (B) */
2899  if (pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected &&
2900  PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer) &&
2901  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount > N_HARD_RESET_COUNT))
2902  {
2903  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
2904  }
2905  else
2906  {
2907  didNothingStepB = 1;
2908  }
2909  break;
2910 
2911  case PSM_PE_SRC_WAIT_NEW_CAPABILITIES: /* (B) */
2912  /* The exit transition is handled by the global state transitions */
2913  didNothingStepB = 1;
2914  break;
2915 
2916  case PSM_PE_SRC_HARD_RESET_RECEIVED: /* (B) */
2917  if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSHardResetTimer))
2918  {
2919  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT;
2920  }
2921  else
2922  {
2923  didNothingStepB = 1;
2924  }
2925  break;
2926 
2927  case PSM_PE_SRC_TRANSITION_TO_DEFAULT: /* (B) */
2928  if (pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V)
2929  {
2930  /* source send hard_reset, 4. after tSrcRecover, open vsafe5v. */
2931  /* source receive hard_reset, 4. after tSrcRecover, open vsafe5v. */
2932  /* 2. wait tSrcRecover */
2933  if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSrcRecoverTimer))
2934  {
2935  pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V = 0;
2936  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SrcTurnOnTypeCVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam,
2937  kVbusPower_InHardReset);
2938 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT) && (PD_CONFIG_VCONN_SUPPORT)
2939 #ifdef USBPD_ENABLE_VCONN_DISCHARGE
2940  PD_DpmDischargeVconn(pdInstance, 0);
2941 #endif
2942  PD_DpmSetVconn(pdInstance, pdInstance->raPresent);
2943 #endif
2944  }
2945  else
2946  {
2947  didNothingStepB = 1;
2948  }
2949  }
2950  /* source send hard_reset, 5. wait vsafe5v. */
2951  /* source receive hard_reset, 5. wait vsafe5v. */
2952  else if (PD_DpmCheckVbus(pdInstance))
2953  {
2954  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SRC_HARD_RESET_REQUEST, NULL, 1);
2955  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer, T_NO_RESPONSE);
2956  pdInstance->enterSrcFromSwap = 0;
2957  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_STARTUP;
2958  }
2959  else
2960  {
2961  /* Wait until the power supply transitions to default. */
2962  didNothingStepB = 0;
2963  }
2964  break;
2965 
2966 #endif
2967 
2968 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_DUAL_POWER_ROLE_ENABLE)
2969  case PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GET_SOURCE_CAP: /* (B) */
2970  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
2971  {
2972  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer);
2973  /* SourceCapabilities and VendorDefined are handled in the global section. */
2974  if ((triggerInfo.pdMsgSop == kPD_MsgSOP) && ((triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgReject) ||
2975  (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgNotSupported)))
2976  {
2977  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GET_SOURCE_CAP)
2978  {
2979  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
2980  }
2981  else
2982  {
2983  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
2984  }
2985 
2986  if (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgReject)
2987  {
2988  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_Reject;
2989  }
2990  else
2991  {
2992  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_NotSupported;
2993  }
2994  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_GET_PARTNER_SRC_CAP_FAIL, &commandResultCallback, 1);
2995  }
2996  else
2997  {
2998  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
2999  }
3000  }
3001  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer))
3002  {
3003  if (pdInstance->psmCurState == PSM_PE_DR_SRC_GET_SOURCE_CAP)
3004  {
3005  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
3006  }
3007  else
3008  {
3009  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
3010  }
3011  }
3012  else
3013  {
3014  didNothingStepB = 1;
3015  }
3016  break;
3017 
3018  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_OFF: /* (B) */
3019  /* check source is standby */
3020  if (PD_DpmCheckVsafe0V(pdInstance))
3021  {
3022  /* NOTE : DPM will actively discharge VBUS, and use a timer to ensure at least a min discharge
3023  * time
3024  */
3025  /* have enter standby */
3026  PD_DpmDischargeVbus(pdInstance, 0);
3027  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_ASSERT_RD;
3028  }
3029  else if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
3030  {
3031  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_CHECK_ASYNC_RX;
3032  }
3033  else
3034  {
3035  didNothingStepB = 0; /* need check vbus constantly */
3036  }
3037  break;
3038 
3039  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_WAIT_SOURCE_ON: /* (B) */
3040  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
3041  {
3042  if ((triggerInfo.pdMsgSop == kPD_MsgSOP) && (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgPsRdy))
3043  {
3044  PD_MsgStopReceive(pdInstance);
3045  PD_TimerClear(pdInstance, tPSSourceOnTimer);
3046  /* Swap from SOURCE to SINK */
3047  /* pr swap end */
3048  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
3049 #if defined(PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_CABLE_COMMUNICATION_ENABLE)
3050  /* Cable plug will need a soft reset */
3051  pdInstance->psmCablePlugResetNeeded = 1;
3052 #endif
3053 
3054  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_SNK_GET_TYPEC_CURRENT_CAP, &inCase32Tmp);
3055  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkDrawTypeCVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam,
3056  (uint8_t)inCase32Tmp, kVbusPower_InPRSwap);
3057  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_PR_SWAP_SUCCESS, NULL, 1);
3058 
3059  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_STARTUP;
3060  }
3061  else
3062  {
3063  /* A protocol error during power role swap triggers a Hard Reset */
3064  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
3065  }
3066  }
3067  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSSourceOnTimer))
3068  {
3069  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
3070  }
3071  else
3072  {
3073  didNothingStepB = 1;
3074  }
3075  break;
3076 
3077  case PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_SEND_PR_SWAP: /* (B) */
3078  {
3079  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
3080  {
3081  switch (triggerInfo.pdMsgType)
3082  {
3083  case kPD_MsgAccept:
3084  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_PRS_SRC_SNK_TRANSITION_TO_OFF;
3085  break;
3086 
3087  case kPD_MsgReject:
3088  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
3089  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_Reject;
3090  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_PR_SWAP_FAIL, &commandResultCallback, 1);
3091  break;
3092 
3093  case kPD_MsgWait:
3094  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
3095  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tPrSwapWaitTimer, T_PRSWAP_WAIT);
3096  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_Wait;
3097  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_PR_SWAP_FAIL, &commandResultCallback, 1);
3098  break;
3099 
3100  default:
3101  if (triggerInfo.pdMsgType != kPD_MsgInvalid)
3102  {
3103  /* SourceCapabilities and VendorDefined are handled in the global section. */
3104  /* soft reset other packets */
3105  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
3106  }
3107  break;
3108  }
3109  }
3110  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer))
3111  {
3112  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SRC_READY;
3113  }
3114  else
3115  {
3116  didNothingStepB = 1;
3117  }
3118  }
3119  break;
3120 #endif
3121 
3122 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_SINK_ROLE_ENABLE)
3123  case PSM_PE_SNK_DISCOVERY: /* (B) */
3124  if (pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected &&
3125  PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer) &&
3126  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount > N_HARD_RESET_COUNT))
3127  {
3128  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
3129  }
3130  else if (pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V)
3131  {
3132  if ((PD_DpmCheckVsafe0V(pdInstance)) ||
3133  (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tPSHardResetTimer)))
3134  {
3135  pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V = 0;
3136  }
3137  else
3138  {
3139  /* No change in state, we should stay in low power mode */
3140  didNothingStepB = 1;
3141  }
3142  }
3143  else if ((PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_GET_VBUS_POWER_STATE, &taskEventSet) ==
3144  kStatus_PD_Success) &&
3145  (taskEventSet & PD_VBUS_POWER_STATE_VBUS_MASK))
3146  {
3147  if (pdInstance->asmHardResetSnkProcessing)
3148  {
3149  pdInstance->asmHardResetSnkProcessing = 0;
3150  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_SNK_GET_TYPEC_CURRENT_CAP, &inCase32Tmp);
3151  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkDrawTypeCVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam,
3152  (uint8_t)inCase32Tmp, kVbusPower_InHardReset);
3153  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SNK_HARD_RESET_REQUEST, NULL, 1);
3154  }
3155 
3156  /* Hard Reset is no longer in progress, allow VBus monitoring */
3157  /* kVbusPower_InHardReset is end */
3158  PD_ConnectSetPowerProgress(pdInstance, kVbusPower_Stable);
3159  pdInstance->psmHardResetNeedsVSafe0V = 0;
3160 
3161  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES;
3162  }

3164  {
3165  /* need check vbus constantly */
3166  didNothingStepB = 0;
3167  }
3168  break;
3169 
3170  case PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES: /* (B) */
3171  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
3172  {
3173  /* SourceCapabilities and VendorDefined are handled in the global section. */
3174  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_SEND_SOFT_RESET;
3175  }
3176  else if (pdInstance->psmPreviouslyPdConnected &&
3177  PD_TimerCheckValidTimeOut(pdInstance, tNoResponseTimer) &&
3178  (pdInstance->psmHardResetCount > N_HARD_RESET_COUNT))
3179  {
3180  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_EXIT_TO_ERROR_RECOVERY;
3181  }

3185  }

3188  case PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY: /* (B) */
3189  {

3196  break;

3200  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_Wait;
3201  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SNK_RDO_FAIL, &commandResultCallback, 1);
3202  if (pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted)
3203  {
3204  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
3205  pdInstance->psmSnkReceiveRdoWaitRetry = 1;
3206  PD_TimerStart(pdInstance, tSinkRequestTimer, T_SINK_REQUEST);
3207  }
3208  else
3209  {
3210  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES;
3211  }
3212  break;

3215  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
3216  commandResultCallback = kCommandResult_Reject;
3217  PD_DpmAppCallback(pdInstance, PD_DPM_SNK_RDO_FAIL, &commandResultCallback, 1);
3218  if (pdInstance->psmExplicitContractExisted)
3219  {
3220  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
3221  }
3222  else
3223  {
3224  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_WAIT_FOR_CAPABILITIES;
3225  }
3226  break;
3227 
3228  default:
3229  if (triggerInfo.pdMsgType != kPD_MsgInvalid)
3230  {
3231  /* SourceCapabilities and VendorDefined are handled in the global section. */
3232  /* soft reset other packets */
3233  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_CHECK_SINK_SOURCE_CAP_RX;
3234  }
3235  break;
3236  }
3237  }
3238  else if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSenderResponseTimer))
3239  {
3240  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
3241  }
3242  else
3243  {
3244  didNothingStepB = 1;
3245  }
3246  }
3247  break;
3248 
3249  case PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY_WAIT_TIMER_TIME_OUT: /* (B) */
3250  if (PD_TimerCheckInvalidOrTimeOut(pdInstance, tSinkRequestTimer))
3251  {
3252  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_SELECT_CAPABILITY;
3253  }
3254  break;
3255 
3256  case PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_SINK: /* (B) */
3257  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)
3258  {
3259  /* SourceCapabilities and VendorDefined are handled in the global section. */
3260  if ((triggerInfo.pdMsgSop == kPD_MsgSOP) && (triggerInfo.pdMsgType == kPD_MsgPing))
3261  {
3262  /* Remain in the same state */
3263  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_TRANSITION_SINK;
3264  }
3265  else
3266  {

3279  pdInstance->callbackFns->PD_SnkDrawRequestVbus(pdInstance->callbackParam,

3283  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_PE_SNK_READY;
3284  }
3285  else
3286  {
3287  pdInstance->psmNewState = PSM_HARD_RESET;
3288  }
3289  }
3290  }

3294  }

3298  /* state machine */
3299 #if (defined PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE) && (PD_CONFIG_VENDOR_DEFINED_MESSAGE_ENABLE)

3303  inCase32Tmp &= Pd_PsmSecondaryStateHandler(pdInstance, 2, kPD_MsgSOPpp, &triggerInfo);
3304  if ((pdInstance->psmSecondaryState[0] != PSM_IDLE) ||

3309  {
3310  didNothingStepB = 0;
3311  }

3316  if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_PD_MSG)

3320  }
3321  else if (triggerInfo.triggerEvent == PSM_TRIGGER_DPM_MSG)
3322  {

3324  PD_PsmSinkRdyProcessDpmMessage(pdInstance, &triggerInfo);
3325  }

uint8_t PD_PsmStateMachine ( pd_instance_t *  pdInstance)
6484 {
6485  uint32_t infoVal;
6486  // error, continue, wait event
6487  uint8_t returnVal = kSM_Continue;
6488 
6489  // dpmStateMachine的作用？ 表示是否进入了DPM State machine ?
6490  switch (pdInstance->dpmStateMachine)
6491  {
6492  // 如果该变量为0，则检查是否有vbus，如果有，设置为1 （这应该是初始化的流程）
6493  case 0:
6494  /* wait vbus charge */
6495  /* Neither Source nor Sink should enter PSM before VSafe5V is available */
6496  PD_PhyControl(pdInstance, PD_PHY_GET_VBUS_POWER_STATE, &infoVal);
6497  if (infoVal & PD_VBUS_POWER_STATE_VBUS_MASK)
6498  {
6499  pdInstance->dpmStateMachine = 1;
6500  }
6501  break;
6502 
6503  case 1:
6504  // 什么情况会unknown, 如果unknown，则置为idle，否则保持
6505  pdInstance->psmNewState = (pdInstance->psmCurState == PSM_UNKNOWN) ? PSM_IDLE : pdInstance->psmCurState;
6506 
6507  /* Did we do anything in Step A or B or C */
6508  /* Step A: common process */
6509  /* Step B: state is not changed */
6510  /* Step C: change to new state */
6511 
6512  // 作用 ？
6513  do
6514  {
6515  returnVal = PD_PsmEnterState(pdInstance);
6516  returnVal = PD_PsmProcessState(pdInstance);
6517  } while (((pdInstance->psmCurState != pdInstance->psmNewState) || (returnVal == kSM_Continue)) &&
6518  (returnVal != kSM_ErrorRecovery));
6519 
6520  if (returnVal == kSM_ErrorRecovery)
6521  {
6522  PD_TimerCancelAllTimers(pdInstance, _tStartTimer, _tMaxDpmTimer);
6523  }
6524  break;
6525 
6526  default:
6527  break;
6528  }
6529 
6530  return returnVal;
6531 }
